1
00:00:03,258 --> 00:00:05,800
GNOME 3.26 is here..

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:09,092
..packed by 6 months of exciting changes by the community.

3
00:00:10,008 --> 00:00:12,550
The shell is GNOME's user interface..

4
00:00:13,383 --> 00:00:16,758
..and this cycle it has received a visual overhaul of its search,..

5
00:00:16,842 --> 00:00:18,675
..giving you a better overview.

6
00:00:20,592 --> 00:00:23,550
GNOME's interface is configured from the control center,..

7
00:00:23,550 --> 00:00:25,008
..which features a new sidebar.

8
00:00:25,217 --> 00:00:27,675
..making it possible to jump between settings easily..

9
00:00:27,675 --> 00:00:29,133
..to find what you are looking for.

10
00:00:30,092 --> 00:00:32,425
A dedicated Wi-Fi area ensures easy..

11
00:00:32,425 --> 00:00:35,217
..and logical access for managing wireless connections.

12
00:00:35,925 --> 00:00:38,383
The Display settings are quicker to access,..

13
00:00:38,383 --> 00:00:39,842
..so you can configure common setups..

14
00:00:39,842 --> 00:00:43,508
.. such as single displays, joint displays and mirror.

15
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:48,675
Many improvements have also landed for GNOME Apps.

16
00:00:49,258 --> 00:00:52,508
Simple Scan has had a redesign of its editing tools.

17
00:00:53,217 --> 00:00:57,675
Polari now comes with an initial setup to get you started quickly..

18
00:00:57,675 --> 00:01:00,717
..and has support for sending and receiving emojis.

19
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:05,175
Logs gained event compression for better overview.

20
00:01:06,217 --> 00:01:10,425
Photos has new zoom controls,..

21
00:01:10,425 --> 00:01:13,217
..and Disks gained the ability to resize partitions..

22
00:01:13,217 --> 00:01:14,758
..and new disk image files.

23
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:21,175
Developers can look forward to big additions in Builder.

24
00:01:21,175 --> 00:01:23,883
It features a new visual design and animations.

25
00:01:24,467 --> 00:01:26,425
An initial built-in debugger enables you..

26
00:01:26,425 --> 00:01:28,758
..to debug application threads and add break points.

27
00:01:29,550 --> 00:01:30,758
..and much more.

28
00:01:33,842 --> 00:01:35,508
GNOME is a worldwide project..

29
00:01:35,508 --> 00:01:38,342
..and with your help we can push software freedom to the next level.

30
00:01:39,383 --> 00:01:42,092
Have a chat with us or read more at gnome.org.
